e\": \"user\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Role: You are an expert JVM test engineer specializing in high-coverage integration testing for external libraries.\\n\\nTask:\\nImprove test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0`.\\n\\nSource Context:\\nCoordinate: com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0\\nRepository URL: https://github.com/lloydmeta/enumeratum\\nMain sources:\\n- URL: https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/enumeratum-macros_3-1.9.0-sources.jar\\n- Local path: local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main\\n- Files available: 4\\n\\n\\n\\nIssue-Requested Metadata:\\nNo reporter-provided missing metadata context was supplied.\\n\\nLibrary Preparation Preflight:\\nLibrary preparation preflight produced setup context.\\n\\nSummary: enumeratum-macros_3 is a Scala 3 compile-time macro implementation normally reached through the public enumeratum_3 API, not by direct Java/runtime calls to the macro classes.\\n\\nAlready applied by Forge:\\n- Add testImplementation dependency com.beachape:enumeratum_3:1.9.0 (applied)\\n\\nAgent guidance:\\nUse Scala 3 test sources that define small enumeratum Enum and, if covering ValueEnumMacros, ValueEnum examples through the public enumeratum API. For Scala 3 ValueEnum coverage, configure the Scala compiler option -Yretain-trees as documented by Enumeratum; otherwise ValueEnum macro use may fail or be incomplete. Do not try to exercise EnumMacros or ValueEnumMacros directly from Java because their public signatures require Scala quoted macro internals.\\n\\nRisks:\\n- The macro implementation runs at Scala test compilation time, while native-image runtime tests may only execute the generated enum code; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether this produces useful reachability coverage.\\n- The Scala 3 compiler version in the artifact POM is 3.3.5; the repos