ata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main/enumeratum-macros_3-1.9.0-sources.jar\\n/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main/extracted/META-INF/MANIFEST.MF\\n/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main/extracted/enumeratum/values/AllowAlias.scala\\n/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main/extracted/enumeratum/EnumMacros.scala\\n/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/main/extracted/enumeratum/ValueEnumMacros.scala\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1782421136852}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-25T20-54-32-322606Z.log:7006:[thinking] **Exploring coverage instrumentation**\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-25T20-54-32-322606Z.log:7008:[thinking] I'm considering whether there's separate coverage instrumentation for compilation. Right now, I can't run it, but dynamic-access coverage might have been generated from the test task using jacoco XML. I wonder if that includes compiler executions, especially if the macro class is instrumented and executed in the Gradle daemon. However, it seems like it's not included in test.exec. There's definitely some complexity in how all of this fits together!\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-25T20-54-32-322606Z.log:7012:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacrosInnerValueOfFromExprTest.scala\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"    assertEquals(None, TicketPriority.withValueOpt(42))\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nsealed abstract class TicketPriority(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\\n\",\"newText\":\"    assertEquals(None, TicketPriority.withValueOpt(42))\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def intValueEnumFindValuesSupportsValuesDeclaredInEntryBodies(): Unit = {\\n    assertEquals(IndexedSeq(BodyBackedCode.Accepted, BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.values)\\n    assertEquals(Map(202 -> BodyBackedCode.Accepted, 409 -> BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.valuesToEntriesMap)\\n    assertSame(BodyBackedCode.Accepted, BodyBackedCode.withValue(202))\\n    assertEquals(Some(BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.withValueOpt(409))\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def intValueEnumFindValuesSupportsScalaThreeEnumCases(): Unit = {\\n    assertEquals(IndexedSeq(ApiStatus.Experimental, ApiStatus.Stable), ApiStatus.values)\\n    assertEquals(Map(10 -> ApiStatus.Experimental, 20 -> ApiStatus.Stable), ApiStatus.valuesToEntriesMap)\\n    assertSame(ApiStatus.Stable, ApiStatus.withValue(20))\\n    assertEquals(Right(ApiStatus.Experimental), ApiStatus.withValueEither(10))\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nsealed abstract class TicketPriority(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\\n\"}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-25T20-54-32-322606Z.log:7013:[tool-call] end id=call_gCzpyb18MBNTbQrmCNMJwlB2|fc_07232d5e63655053016a3d96a9259c81939f35784f703434c4 name=edit args={\"path\": \"tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacrosInnerValueOfFromExprTest.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    assertEquals(None, TicketPriority.withValueOpt(42))\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nsealed abstract class TicketPriority(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\\n\", \"newText\": \"    assertEquals(None, TicketPriority.withValueOpt(42))\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def intValueEnumFindValuesSupportsValuesDeclaredInEntryBodies(): Unit = {\\n    assertEquals(IndexedSeq(BodyBackedCode.Accepted, BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.values)\\n    assertEquals(Map(202 -> BodyBackedCode.Accepted, 409 -> BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.valuesToEntriesMap)\\n    assertSame(BodyBackedCode.Accepted, BodyBackedCode.withValue(202))\\n    assertEquals(Some(BodyBackedCode.Rejected), BodyBackedCode.withValueOpt(409))\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def intValueEnumFindValuesSupportsScalaThreeEnumCases(): Unit = {\\n    assertEquals(IndexedSeq(ApiStatus.Experimental, ApiStatus.Stable), ApiStatus.values)\\n    assertEquals(Map(10 -> ApiStatus.Experimental, 20 -> ApiStatus.Stable), ApiStatus.valuesToEntriesMap)\\n    assertSame(ApiStatus.Stable, ApiStatus.withValue(20))\\n    assertEquals(Right(ApiStatus.Experimental), ApiStatus.withValueEither(10))\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nsealed abstract class TicketPriority(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\\n\"}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.beachape:enumeratum-macros_3:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-25T20-54-32-322606Z.log:7014:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring coverage instrumentation**\\n\\nI'm considering whether there's separate coverage instrumentation for compilation. Right now, I can't run it, but dynamic-access coverage might have been generated from the test task using jacoco XML. I wonder if that includes compiler executions, especially if the macro class is instrumented and executed in the Gradle daemon. However, it seems like it's not included in test.exec. There's definitely some complexity in how all of this fits together!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_07232d5e63655053016a3d96931a288193b90a2b4b793faa87\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqPZapoKQ62UpzJitcgxVeA-objirUaAm_K841B95SLHw_znDX0s5-Z5bWl9PbLd0oKqlWKdQ29rSec-qKuzuO6bVihjx4O3a6McB9AwiABaARovnXlaf0HWm2PgMSR8zlpDni7_