\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test compilation**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether tests compile outside the agent. In the metadata repo, dynamic-access coverage relies on traces from Java execution. The build might generate metadata by running with the native-image-agent attached only during Gradle test processes. The Scala compiler could run before tests and might not be instrumented. However, if the agent attaches to the entire Gradle, all source dynamic calls during compilation might be covered. It’s noted that the task recognizes macro execution at Scala test compilation time. I wonder if we should include a note stating “No metadata modified.”\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_fnx7sQhlNL2wWBpA9jRmW7av|fc_07232d5e63655053016a3d9560da4c8193a7be02f69961fe23\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/build.gradle\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 751, \"output\": 412, \"cacheRead\": 33792, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 34955, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1782420824346, \"responseId\": \"resp_07232d5e63655053016a3d9558b47481939d2a79c022b3182c\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_fnx7sQhlNL2wWBpA9jRmW7av|fc_07232d5e63655053016a3d9560da4c8193a7be02f69961fe23\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\nplugins {\\n    id \\\"org.graalvm.internal.tck\\\"\\n    id \\\"scala\\\"\\n}\\n\\nString libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\nint testJvmVersion = tck.testJvmVersion.get()\\nString scala3Version = tck.s